Install Operator:
1.Install Red Hat OpenShift GitOps operator (This will be installed to the openshift-gitops-operator namespace, however resources will be created under openshift-operator namespace)
2. edit argocd yaml to add ocp-admins as a group who can access argocd
2.Fetch the route from openshift-operator namespace--> Login using openshift credentials

Configure Gitops
1.Create project
2.Configure Repository
3. Create application


1. Namespace must be created
2. run the below command for every namespace/project to be created
   oc adm policy add-role-to-user admin system:serviceaccount:openshift-gitops:openshift-gitops-argocd-application-controller -n project-name